title: Knee Arthroplasty Surgery ICD9CM
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values identifies patients who have a surgical procedure of a knee arthroplasty.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have a knee arthroplasty procedure.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the Procedure category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Only use codes which represent knee arthroplasty surgical procedures.  Codes used are to be ICD9CM codes only.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet the inclusion criteria.)
